oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Homestead way to grow raspberries and blackberries
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Nine page foldout booklet which provides detailed instructions on growing raspberries and blackberries the homestead way, with details on diseases. The first page has illustrations showing pruning and propagation. The booklet includes an order form for various other booklets and a credit slip for $13.00, with envelope, from The Country Bookstore in Noroton, Connecticut.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Palmer, Walt
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Kitchen gardens; Agriculture; Gardening
Raspberries; Berries; Fruit; Food; Homesteading
